--------------- sEPD Cosmics Analysis -----------------

Only once, make the following directories:
  mkdir ./root
  mkdir ./final_plots

Here are the directions for running this analysis

0. Make root file from prdf (in highbay server)

  0.1 First copy the prdf file (from the va095 -> highbaygw server -> RCF) Note: run this in highbaygw 
    $ scp phnxrc@va095:/home/phnxrc/emcalsectortestdata/cosmic/cosmic_000#####-0000.prdf . # va095 -> highbay
    $ sftp [user name]@sftp.sdcc.bnl.gov:/sphenix/data/data02/sphenix/cemc/sepd/cosmic/ <<< $'put ./cosmic_000#####-0000.prdf' # highbaygw -> rcf

  0.2 run the following script to make a root file from the prdf file on RCF
    $ cd /sphenix/data/data02/sphenix/cemc/sectortest/root/
    $ ../wd409_sectortest/wd409 <prdf file> # e.g. ../wd409_sectortest/wd409 /sphenix/data/data02/sphenix/cemc/sepd/cosmic/cosmic_00023046-0000.prdf

1. Make directory in sepd_mip_plots/cosmics_s##

2. Edit cosmics_config.config (directions are in the file)

3. Run:
   $ root sEPD_Cosmics_Analysis.C
   
   This puts histograms in ./root/outfile_[top sector]_[bottom_sector].root

4. Run:    
   $ root sEPD_Cosmics_Fitting.C

   This	puts histograms and fits in ./root/hists_and_fits_[top sector]_[bottom_sector].root

5. Run:     
   $ root sEPD_Cosmics_Draw.C

   This puts plots in ./sepd_mip_plots/cosmics_s##/

